And the righteous shall be glad and rejoice in the light of YHWH forever. The elect shall inherit the earth and dwell therein in peace and joy. The name of YHWH shall be praised among all generations and all the holy ones shall bless Him. Peace to the righteous and salvation to those who walk in the ways of the Most High. This is the end of the vision of Enoch the scribe.
The Lord of Spirits will execute judgment upon all and the wicked shall be driven into the darkness and the abyss while the righteous shall shine like the stars forever. The Son of Man sits upon the throne of glory and all the kings and mighty ones shall fall down before Him and worship. The books are opened and the deeds of all flesh are weighed. The Elect One judges the nations and the Watchers receive their eternal sentence.
In those days the Son of Man was named before the Head of Days and the stars and the righteous rejoice in His light. The heaven and earth are transformed and the righteous dwell in eternal light. The elect ones stand before the throne and the books of the living are opened.
And I Enoch saw the secrets of the lightning and the thunder the chambers of the hail and the storehouses of the snow the foundations of the mountains and the rivers of fire. I saw the angels who rule the seasons and the courses of the stars. And the angel showed me all the hidden things of heaven and earth.
And the angel took me and showed me the place of the righteous and the place of the wicked the tree of life and the tree of wisdom. I saw the fallen Watchers bound in the valleys of fire and the women who sinned with them suffering torment. I saw the giants and the spirits that proceed from them afflicting mankind until the day of judgment.
And in the days of Jared my father the Watchers descended upon Mount Hermon and took wives among the daughters of men and taught them forbidden arts and sorcery. They begat giants who devoured mankind and filled the earth with violence and blood. And the earth cried out to heaven and the four archangels brought the cry before the Most High.
In the beginning when the children of men multiplied the Watchers the sons of heaven saw the daughters of men and lusted after them. And they said to one another “Come let us choose wives from among the children of men and beget children.” And two hundred of them descended upon Mount Hermon in the days of Jared.
The words of the blessing of Enoch according to which he blessed the elect and righteous who will be living in the day of tribulation when all the wicked and godless are to be removed.
